The paper discusses the use of machine learning, specifically deep neural networks and reinforcement learning, to solve combinatorial optimization problems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of attention models, which is a popular technique in natural language processing and computer vision, indicating a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The problem being addressed is the vehicle routing problem, which is a subfield of robotics and control (cs.RO). The use of dynamic encoder-decoder architecture suggests a possible connection to neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning and dynamic attention models suggests a possible connection to control systems (cs.SY).
